</div>

<h4 id="optimisation">Optimisation</h4>

<p>It turns out that hardcoding assets and removing functionality doesnâ€™t do too much for reducing file size. Feel free to <a href="http://github.com/dannyalright/contextkit/blob/master/examples/SpringBoard%20App%20iPhone%207.origami">download the iPhone 7-only version</a> if you want to take a look or see what else can be stripped-out.</p>

<h3 id="notification-component">Notification component</h3>

<p>A drop-down notification component for Origami. Uses responsive-sizing, so can be used on an iPad, too.</p>

<!-- Wrapping in div necessary to avoid Markdown rendering as <code> -->
<div class="media video">
  
  <video src="/assets/posts/2017-08-17-contextkit-for-origami/notification-springboard-app.mp4" playsinline="" controls="" muted=""></video>

  <!-- Caption -->
  
  <label>The Notification component tied to the SpringBoard App component.</label>
  
</div>

<p>To open an app from the Notification component, simply use an Interaction patch with Notification as the target layer and connect it to the Open App input on the SpringBoard App component.</p>

<!-- Wrapping in div necessary to avoid Markdown rendering as <code> -->
<div class="media">
   
  <!-- Host images locally by default -->
  <img data-src="/assets/posts/2017-08-17-contextkit-for-origami/notification-app-open.jpg" />
   
</div>

<p>You donâ€™t need to use it with my SpringBoard App component, if you just want to test with notifications.</p>

<h3 id="deep-link-template">Deep Link template</h3>

<p>A simple template for emulating the app-switching behavior in iOS. Drop your prototype contents into the â€˜Your Appâ€™ group, and customise the â€˜Some Other Appâ€™ group to your heartâ€™s content.</p>

